The paper deals with algorithms and structural results related to polynomial decomposition, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of dense representation and bit size analysis suggests information theory (cs.IT) as a possible sub-category. The study of multivariate cases and the mention of distinctness assumptions suggest control theory (cs.SY) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of structural results and algorithms related to optimization suggest computational geometry (cs.CG) as a possible sub-category.
